## Description {#details}

In what follows, the term &quot;input IR&quot; refers to code that is fed into the vectorizer whereas the term &quot;output IR&quot; refers to code that is generated by the vectorizer.

<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/vplane">VPLane</a> provides a way to access lanes in both fixed width and scalable vectors, where for the latter the lane index sometimes needs calculating as a runtime expression.

Definition at line 154 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/transforms/lib/transforms/vectorize/vplan-h">VPlan.h</a>.

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>enum class llvm::VPLane::Kind : uint8&#95;t</>}
 labels = {["strong"]}>
<a href="#afb4648a83781e7ee62f34771ea338c29">Kind</a> describes how to interpret Lane.

<EnumerationList title="Enumeration values">

<Link id="afb4648a83781e7ee62f34771ea338c29a7fb55ed0b7a30342ba6da306428cae04" />
<EnumerationListItem name="First">
For First, Lane is the index into the first N elements of a fixed-vector &lt;N x &lt;ElTy&gt;&gt; or a scalable vector &lt;vscale x N x &lt;ElTy&gt;&gt;
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="afb4648a83781e7ee62f34771ea338c29a69d68d161f986e83192f701108a729bc" />
<EnumerationListItem name="ScalableLast">
For ScalableLast, Lane is the offset from the start of the last N-element subvector in a scalable vector &lt;vscale x N x &lt;ElTy&gt;&gt;
</EnumerationListItem>

</EnumerationList>
